    "created_at": "2026-02-19T10:50:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-02-19T10:50:57Z",
    "body": "Use `$line_break` instead of \\n. The `$line_break` calculates the right  amount of character for `$all` if using `$fill`.\n\nTry this:\n```toml\nformat = \"\"\"\n╭─\\\n$os[](fg:white bg:black)\\\n$username[@](fg:yellow bg:black)\\\n$hostname[](fg:black) \\\n$directory\\\n$git_branch\\\n$git_state\\\n$git_status\\\n$fill\\\n$all─╮\\\n$line_break\\\n╰─$character\n\"\"\"\n\nright_format = \"\"\"─╯\"\"\"\n\n[line_break]\ndisabled = false\n```\n\nI have tried that, and it solve your `$fill$all` issue",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
